My name is Angel Daniel Lara-Suarez and I am 25 years old attending Eastern Washington University as Visual Communication Design major.
My heritage consists half Mexican from my mom side and half Honduran from my dad side.

I am kind hearted and I like to help others in any way possible that is within my power. I go above and beyond to some friends that I have a close relationship with. I am a hard worker with the ability to learn new skills and be able to apply it to a daily life.

I was born and raised in Yakima Washington on May 1 1993 and have lived there most of life. I moved to Ellensburg after I graduated from high school and lived there for 2 1/2 years. I returned back to Yakima for 2 more years before moving to Cheney Washington.

I have 2 siblings. One older half brother from my dad side; His name is Angel as well and he is currently living in Honduras. He is 29 years and has a daughter. My younger brotherâ€™s name is Likhi who turned 14 in August and began his first year of high school.

I graduated from Eisenhower High school in Yakima and attend Central Washington University for Accounting. I was there for 2 1/2 years and after went back to Yakima to attend at Yakima Valley Community College. I was there for 2 years and graduated with my Associates degree in Arts. My plans were to go to Heritage University for Secondary Education in Mathematics but decided to attend Eastern Washington University as a Secondary Education Mathematics; however, I changed to Visual Communication Design with the User Interface certificate.
